Testing of SLICE additional notifications.

1. Navigate here to create a new record: https://cmudev01.service-now.com/nav_to.do?uri=%2Fx_camu_cmu_install_installation_applications.do%3Fsys_id%3D-1%26sys_is_list%3Dtrue%26sys_target%3Dx_camu_cmu_install_installation_applications%26sysparm_checked_items%3D%26sysparm_fixed_query%3D%26sysparm_group_sort%3D%26sysparm_list_css%3D%26sysparm_query%3D%26sysparm_referring_url%3Dx_camu_cmu_install_installation_applications_list.do%253fsysparm_clear_stack%253dtrue%26sysparm_target%3D%26sysparm_view%3D
2. Fill out the mandatory fields on the record.
3. Add an approval group for the Approvers
4. Click the UI Action set to Submitted.
5. As a admin navigate to https://cmudev01.service-now.com/nav_to.do?uri=%2Fsys_email_list.do%3Fsysparm_userpref_module%3D0271f5510a0a0b6100921bb97ead33ac%26sysparm_view%3Dsent%26sysparm_query%3Dmailbox%3Dsent%5Esys_created_onONToday@javascript:gs.daysAgoStart(0)@javascript:gs.daysAgoEnd(0)%5EEQ%26sysparm_clear_stack%3Dtrue
6. Click the ‘Created’ column to sort by most recently created
7. Find the email with the recipient kpalko@andrew.cmu.edu and a subject of (number) -  Application for Test has been submitted. Click into this email by clicking the date.
8. Scroll down to the related links and click ‘Preview HTML body’ and review the email body.
9. Navigate back to the installation application previously created.
10. Add a comment in the ‘Additional Comments’ variable and click ‘Post’
11. As a admin navigate to https://cmudev01.service-now.com/nav_to.do?uri=%2Fsys_email_list.do%3Fsysparm_userpref_module%3D0271f5510a0a0b6100921bb97ead33ac%26sysparm_view%3Dsent%26sysparm_query%3Dmailbox%3Dsent%5Esys_created_onONToday@javascript:gs.daysAgoStart(0)@javascript:gs.daysAgoEnd(0)%5EEQ%26sysparm_clear_stack%3Dtrue
12. Click the ‘Created’ column to sort by most recently created
13. Find the email with the recipient kpalko@andrew.cmu.edu and a subject of (number) -  Application for Test has a new comment. Click into this email by clicking the date.
14. Scroll down to the related links and click ‘Preview HTML body’ and review the email body.
15. Navigate back to the installation application previously created.
16. Click the ‘Status’ dropdown and change to ‘Approved’ and save the record.
17. As a admin navigate to https://cmudev01.service-now.com/nav_to.do?uri=%2Fsys_email_list.do%3Fsysparm_userpref_module%3D0271f5510a0a0b6100921bb97ead33ac%26sysparm_view%3Dsent%26sysparm_query%3Dmailbox%3Dsent%5Esys_created_onONToday@javascript:gs.daysAgoStart(0)@javascript:gs.daysAgoEnd(0)%5EEQ%26sysparm_clear_stack%3Dtrue
18. Click the ‘Created’ column to sort by most recently created
19. Find the email with the recipient kpalko@andrew.cmu.edu and a subject of (number) -  (short description) has been approved
20. Scroll down to the related links and click ‘Preview HTML body’ and review the email body.
21. Navigate back to the installation application previously created.
22. Click the ‘Status’ dropdown and change to ‘Approved’ and save the record.
23. As a admin navigate to https://cmudev01.service-now.com/nav_to.do?uri=%2Fsys_email_list.do%3Fsysparm_userpref_module%3D0271f5510a0a0b6100921bb97ead33ac%26sysparm_view%3Dsent%26sysparm_query%3Dmailbox%3Dsent%5Esys_created_onONToday@javascript:gs.daysAgoStart(0)@javascript:gs.daysAgoEnd(0)%5EEQ%26sysparm_clear_stack%3Dtrue
24. Click the ‘Created’ column to sort by most recently created
25. Find the email with the recipient kpalko@andrew.cmu.edu and a subject of (number) -  Application for Test has been withdrawn. Click into this email by clicking the date.
26. Scroll down to the related links and click ‘Preview HTML body’ and review the email body.
